## ЁЯФР Access & Security Guards

Every Company method that performs an action checks two things before proceeding:

### Check 1 тАФ Must Be Logged In
```java
if (!isLoggedIn()) {
    System.out.println("[ERROR] You must be logged in to post a challenge.");
    return null;
}
```
`isLoggedIn()` is a method inherited from `User`. A Company cannot create, edit, or close challenges without an active session.

### Check 2 тАФ Must Be Verified (for challenge creation)
```java
if (!isVerified()) {
    System.out.println("[ERROR] Your account must be verified by Admin before posting challenges.");
    return null;
}
```
`isVerified()` is also inherited from `User`. It is set to `true` only when an `Admin` calls `setVerified(true)` on the account. This prevents fake or unverified companies from flooding the platform with challenges.

